Axial.summary: This worksheet is a glulam column design calculator for combined axial load and bending, producing utilization checks from user-defined loads, geometry, and material/adjustment factors. It is used during preliminary and detailed design to size a glulam column and verify governing limit states for the selected loading case (e.g., axial-only or axial+bending). Grey cells with red text are the engineer-controlled inputs (loads, tributary area, member dimensions, species/grade, and adjustment factors), while the remaining cells compute derived actions, section properties, resistances, and utilization ratios. The sheet embeds clause references and table lookups consistent with CSA O86-style member design, and it is intended for rapid iteration and sanity-checking rather than replacing engineering judgement. Use it when you need a transparent, auditable calculation trail from inputs → intermediate calculations → final results/utilization outputs for a single column/member.

Guidance Tables.summary: This worksheet contains the supporting reference tables used by the design sheet (material properties, section factors, and lookup data). It is not intended for direct user input during routine checks; instead it drives dropdowns and table lookups in the main calculation sheet. Most values here are static tabulated data and are referenced by formulas elsewhere in the workbook. Change these tables only when updating the workbook to a new edition of reference data or when calibrating to a specific manufacturer/grade set. Use this sheet when you need to audit where a property value comes from or to extend the workbook to additional grades/sizes.
